   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>IV.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE PRACTICE OF PREACHING</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>THE GOSPEL</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>PRAY BRINGING PEOPLE TO GOD</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>First, make a list of all the names of relatives, friends, schoolmates, colleagues, and contacts for whom the Lord has burdened you.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Then pray for them one by one until they are saved.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>PRAY IN FAITH</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Faith is to receive God s promise without doubting during our prayer.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Since it is God who desires that we pray, He has to answer our prayers.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>He said:</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Ask and it shall be given to you; seek and you shall find; knock and it shall be opened to you.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Matthew 7:7</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>PREACH BRINGING GOD TO MAN</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>1 The principle</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The principle of preaching the gospel is to spread from Jerusalem to the remotest part of the earth, from the center to the circumference.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>For this reason, our preaching should start with our close relatives and friends and continue to spread out.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Go to your house, to your own people, and report to them the things the Lord has done to you, and how He has had mercy on you.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Mark 5:19</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Please remember these points:</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Continue in a spirit of prayer.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Have a sincere and earnest attitude.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Present the truth wisely.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Avoid unnecessary debates.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>2 Preach in season and out of season</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Preach the word; be ready in season and out of season; reprove, rebuke, exhort, with all longsuffering and teaching.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>2 Timothy 4:2</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Whenever an opportunity arises and you meet some people, you should follow the inner feeling and speak to them.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>3 Distribute tracts</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Keep gospel tracts handy and pass them out at every opportunity.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>4 Contact people regularly</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Schedule appropriate times, preferably one to two hours a week, for contacting people and preaching the gospel.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>5 Invite people to come to hear the gospel</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>By means of phone calls, letters, or invitations, contact at scheduled times those for whom you pray according to the list you made, inviting them to some meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>You can also give them some Bibles, gospel booklets, or tracts.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Dear saint, since you have believed in the Lord, don t you desire to be the Lord s witness?</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Put down twelve names of your close relatives, friends, and schoolmates:</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>If you will pray for them with faith and persevere in preaching the gospel, in due time you will bear fruit and glorify God.</S>
   </TEXT>
